<TITLE> DU students' outfit calls for class boycott </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 09 (bdnews24.com)Chhatra Bandhu, a newfound students' outfit, has urged Dhaka University students to boycott classes and exams for Thursday to press the release of DU students and teachers from jail. In a statement Wednesday, the organisation threatened to launch a class boycott programme for an indefinite period if the demand was not met immediately. It blamed "apathy" of the DU authorities for the delay in freeing the teachers and students arrested on charges of having roles in the August campus violence. bdnew
